The paper discusses a new paradigm for wireless communication environments using software-defined metasurfaces, which can control and mitigate path loss and multi-path fading effects. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), multimedia (cs.MM), systems and control (cs.SY), and electromagnetics (cs.EM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
